'''''Simplemente Lo Mejor''''' is a [[greatest hits album]] by [[Guatemala]]n singer-songwriter [[Ricardo Arjona]] that was released on 2 December 2008. The album is composed of Arjona's number-one hits, drawn from ''[[Animal Nocturno]]'' (1993) to ''[[Galer<U+00ED>a Caribe]]'' (2000). It served as his final project under the [[Sony Music]] label after signing a contract with [[Warner Music]] in 2008. A CD+DVD and a DVD edition of the album were released in several countries; these included a collection of music videos for the compilation's songs.

''Simplemente Lo Mejor'' was made available one month after the release of Arjona's eleventh studio album, ''[[5to Piso]]'' (2008). This led to speculation that the labels were in a fight to win Arjona's fanbase and sales. ''Simplemente Lo Mejor'' reached number seven on the [[Mexican Albums Chart]], the US [[Billboard Latin Pop Albums|''Billboard'' Latin Pop Albums]] chart and number 33 on the [[Billboard Top Latin Albums|''Billboard'' Top Latin Albums]] chart. It was awarded platinum certifications in Argentina and Mexico.

==Background and release==
[[File:Concierto Ricardo Arjona Miami 2009 crop.jpg|thumb|190px|right|Despite Arjona signing a record deal in 2008 with [[Warner Music]], ''Simplemente Lo Mejor'' was released by Sony Music.|alt=Ricardo Arjona, singing into a microphone]]
===Background===
After spending the majority of his career signed to [[Sony Music Entertainment|Sony]] and [[Sony BMG]], Arjona signed a long-term recording deal with [[Warner Music Latina]]<ref name=leila1>Cobo, Leila (22 September 2008). [http://www.billboard.com/news/ricardo-arjona-signs-with-warner-music-latina-1003853422.story#/news/ricardo-arjona-signs-with-warner-music-latina-1003853422.story "Ricardo Arjona Signs With Warner Music Latina"]. Billboard. Retrieved on 23 March 2012.</ref> in September 2008.<ref name=leila1/> I<U+00F1>igo Zabala, chairman of [[Warner Music Latina|Warner Music Latin America]] commented that "he's an artist that fits perfectly with our company"; he also stated "We are a label that has a major catalog of songwriters and quality pop and rock from the likes of [[Man<U+00E1>]], [[Alejandro Sanz]], [[Laura Pausini]], and now, Arjona."<ref name=leila1/> Arjona announced his eleventh studio album, ''[[5to Piso]]'', on 18 November 2008. In the first month of retail sales, approximately 200,000 copies were purchased; it went Platinum in Mexico,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.entretienes.com/internaCont_idc_297393_id_cat_250.html |title=Ricardo Arjona recibe disco de oro por ventas en M<U+00E9>xico |date=20 November 2008  |work=Entretienes.com |accessdate=10 April 2011}}</ref><ref>[http://www.jornadanet.com/Hemeroteca/n.php?a=23751-1&f=20081120 "Ricardo Arjona recibe disco de oro por sus 50.000 copias vendidas en M<U+00E9>xico"]. ''JornadaNet.com''. Retrieved 1 October 2011.</ref> the United States<ref>[http://www.eltiempo.com.ec/noticias-cuenca/10384-ricardo-arjona-recibe-disco-de-platino/ "Ricardo Arjona recibe Disco de Platino"]. ''eltiempo.com.ec''. Retrieved 1 October 2011.</ref> and several other countries.<ref name=Uni134>[http://musica.univision.com/noticias/article/2008-11-26/arjona-logro-estos-reconocimientos-por "Arjona logr<U+00F3> estos reconocimientos por las altas ventas que su nuevo disco."]. ''Univisi<U+00F3>n''. Retrieved 30 April 2012.</ref> It debuted at number one on Top Latin Albums, becoming his second chart-topper on that list, and sold more than one million copies worldwide.<ref>[http://www.nacion.com/2010-07-29/Entretenimiento/UltimaHora/Entretenimiento2465948.aspx "Ricardo Arjona se pone tropical en su nuevo disco"]. La Naci<U+00F3>n. Retrieved on 11 May 2012.</ref> The album received a [[Grammy Award]] nomination for [[Grammy Award for Best Latin Pop Album|Best Latin Pop Album]] and a [[Latin Grammy Awards of 2009|Latin Grammy Award]] nomination for [[Latin Grammy Award for Best Singer-Songwriter Album|Best Singer-Songwriter Album]].<ref name=LatinGrammy2009>{{cite web|url=http://www.terra.com/musica/noticias/conoce_a_los_nominados_a_los_grammy_latinos/oci701873|title=Conoce a los nominados a los Grammy Latinos|publisher=Terra Networks M<U+00E9>xico|date=19 September 2009|accessdate=28 January 2011|page=2|language=Spanish}}</ref>

===Release===
While [[Warner Music]] released Arjona's new studio album, [[Sony Music]] released ''Simplemente Lo Mejor''. This led to speculation that the labels were in a fight to win his fanbase and sales.<ref>(19 November 2008). [http://sonfamosos.com/2008/11/19/sony-bmg-y-warner-music-se-pelean-por-fans-de-ricardo-arjona/ "Sony BMG y Warner Music se pelean por fans de Ricardo Arjona"]. Son Famosos. Retrieved on 23 March 2012.</ref> ''5to Piso'' hit shelves on 18 November 2008 in the United States,<ref>[http://itunes.apple.com/us/album/5to-piso/id295599869 "5to Piso by Ricardo Arjona"]. [[iTunes]]. [[Apple, Inc.]] Retrieved on 10 May 2012.</ref> and ''Simplemente Lo Mejor'' followed on 2 December 2008.<ref name="ITUS"/> A CD+DVD edition and a DVD edition of the album were released that same day in the United States<ref name="USCD"/><ref name="USDVD"/> and Spain.<ref>[http://www.amazon.es/Simplemente-Lo-Mejor-Ricardo-Arjona/dp/B001IZID6E/ref=sr_1_14?ie=UTF8&qid=1351372526&sr=8-14 "Simplemente Lo Mejor: Ricardo Arjona"]. Amazon.com Retrieved on 10 May 2012.</ref><ref>[http://www.amazon.es/Simplemente-Lo-Mejor-Ricardo-Arjona/dp/B001IYURKA/ref=sr_1_29?ie=UTF8&qid=1351372538&sr=8-29 "Simplemente Lo Mejor (CD/DVD): Ricardo Arjona"]. Amazon.com Retrieved on 10 May 2012.</ref> At that time, [[Univisi<U+00F3>n]] named ''Simplemente Lo Mejor'' "a true collector's item that every fan of Arjona or just happy to his poetry should not be without."<ref>{{cite web|title=Ricardo Arjona lanza un <U+00E1>lbum con todos sus <U+00E9>xitos|url=http://musica.univision.com/noticias/article/2008-12-17/ricardo-arjona-lanza-un-album|work=''Unisivi<U+00F3>n Musica''|publisher=Univision Communications Inc.|accessdate=27 October 2012|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6BjgFkT3f|archivedate=27 October 2012|location=Mexico|language=Spanish}}</ref>

{{clear}}

==Commercial performance==
''Simplemente Lo Mejor'' entered the [[Top 100 Mexico]] at number 35 the week of its debut. The following week, the album jumped to number 17 and, on its third week of release, reached its peak of number seven. It spent three weeks inside the top ten and 27 weeks on the chart.<ref name="MEX">[http://www.mexicancharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Ricardo+Arjona&titel=Simplemente...+lo+mejor&cat=a "Ricardo Arjona&nbsp;<U+2013> Simplemente Lo Mejor"]. Mexicancharts.com. Hung Medien. Retrieved 30 May 2012.</ref> On the US ''Billboard'' Top Latin Albums chart, the album attained a peak of number 33 and stayed on the chart for 70 weeks.<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/#/artist/Ricardo+Arjona/chart-history/29908?f=330&g=Albums "Ricardo Arjona Album & Song Chart History"]. ''Billboard'' [[Latin Albums]] for [[Ricardo Arjona]]. [[Prometheus Global Media]]. Retrieved 30 May 2012.</ref> It performed better on the Latin Pop Albums component chart, where it reached a peak of number seven, remaining on the chart for 88 weeks.<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/#/artist/Ricardo+Arjona/chart-history/29908?f=295&g=Albums "Ricardo Arjona Album & Song Chart History"]. ''Billboard'' [[Latin Pop Albums]] for [[Ricardo Arjona]]. [[Prometheus Global Media]]. Retrieved 30 May 2012.</ref> ''Simplemente Lo Mejor'' was awarded a platinum certification in Argentina and Mexico for 40,000 copies sold and shipped, respectively.<ref name="ArgentinaRicardo_ArjonaSimplemente_Lo_MejoralbumCertRef"/><ref name="MexicoRicardo_ArjonaSimplemente_Lo_MejoralbumCertRef"/>

